text: 1201 Third Avenue (formerly Washington Mutual Tower) is a , 55-story skyscraper in Seattle, in the U.S. state of Washington. It is the third- tallest building in the city, the eighth-tallest on the West Coast of the United States, and the 97th-tallest in the United States. ==References== Category:Buildings and structures in Seattle Category:Skyscrapers in the United States
